post_text: This is the Year of the Teacher, and today is also September 11th. This is a day to remember and be proud of first responders, military members, and other public servants. Pictured below is Marble Falls High School Science teacher Ms. Hinojosa. She is also know as Lt. Colonel Michelle Hinojosa of the National Guard. Today is her last day on campus for a while as she is being deployed to complete a tour in the Middle East. God bless our first responders, their families, our military personnel and families, and God bless Lt. Colonel Hinojosa!

post_text:
La Transferencia Electrónica de Beneficios por Pandemia (P-EBT, por sus siglas en inglés) es un beneficio de alimentos único para las familias que perdieron el acceso a comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido debido al cierre de las escuelas. A fin de mayo, las escuelas les enviarán instrucciones para realizar una solicitud a las familias elegibles para la P-EBT. La solicitud de la P-EBT estará disponible la primera semana de junio.
Los beneficios de alimentos de la P-EBT son para los niños que recibieron beneficios de alimentos del Programa Asistencial de Nutrición Suplementaria (SNAP, por sus siglas en inglés) para marzo de 2020 y para los niños que estén certificados para recibir comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido en Texas durante el año escolar 2019-20. Para obtener más información, visite: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions during device pick up this week. The P-EBT applications will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text: Out of an abundance of caution, Marble Falls ISD is temporarily closing the Middle School meal distribution site. The District is closing this site because an employee who works in that area has been tested for COVID-19. To be clear, we DO NOT know that the employee has COVID-19, only that the employee has been tested. I want to remind you that our food preparation staff has been consistently wearing mask, gloves, and taking other safety/sanitation precautions to maintain a safe and healthy service environment. We will have all employees who have been in contact with this employee self-quarantine pending the test results. Our plan to is sanitize/deep clean the Middle School kitchen and service area, as has been our daily practice, and replace the current food service crew with a group of employees that has not been in contact with the employee who is being tested. With this in mind, we intend to re-open the Middle School meal service site tomorrow, May 13th, 2020.

post_text:
We are excited about the launch of remote learning Monday March, 30 2020 (for details go to https://www.marblefallsisd.org/remotelearning). Using virtual platforms for instruction will allow parents to “sit in on” instruction like never before. We welcome this increased level of parental participation in the learning process, but there are few things to be mindful of:
1. Instruction is for students and limiting distraction so all learners can focus is appreciated.
2. Student questions are productive and appropriate during lessons, questions from parents should occur outside of the “classroom” setting.
3. Parent interactions during virtual classes should be limited to their student.
4. All laws pertaining to student privacy rights will be maintained during virtual instruction.

Due to the Stay In Place order effective 11:59pm tonight, the scheduled pickup for tomorrow is cancelled.

If you already have a device at home personal or otherwise, you are not required to pick one up, as any device will work, since everything can be access online through Classlink.
We will be starting pickup again tonight from 4-8pm. Again, if you have a device(laptop, desktop, iPad, Chromebook) already, you are not required to pick one up. However, if you do not have anything for your student to use, please come pick one up tonight.

Just a reminder, if you are needing to pick up a device for your student:

Elementary student devices can be picked up from their home campus from 4-8pm

Secondary(HS and MS) devices can be picked up at the front of the Middle School from 4-8pm

If you have any questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to reach out to us via email at technology@mfisd.txed.net or by phone at 830-798-3631

post_text:
Hello Again!

In an effort to get the devices in your hands as quickly as possible, we would like to highly encourage you to show up tomorrow Wednesday 3/25 if you are planning on picking up a device for your student. Pickup will start as before at 8a.m. - 12p.m. and again at 4p.m. - 6:30p.m. We will extend the evening time slot if there are parents still trying to pick up a device.

We are also going to open up the Secondary Student pick up at the Middle School tomorrow Wednesday 3/25 from 9a.m. - 12p.m. and again at 4p.m. - 6:30p.m. instead of Friday. This will give us the opportunity to open Friday back up if needed.

This is not mandatory. If you already have a device at home(Laptop, chromebook, desktop, ipad etc) you do not have to come pick one up. You should be able to access all content on your personal devices as well.

Again, if you are planning on picking up a device, please do you best to grab it sooner rather than later! Do not wait until Thursday!

MFISD Technology Dept.

Chris Allen
Superintendent

The Marble Falls ISD Construction Trades Program in partnership with the Highland Lakes Division of the Hill Country Builders Association have constructed a 200 sq. ft. fully functional 1BR/1BA home, completely finished, including appliances!
It will be going up for auction soon! Please contact Dr. Wes Cunningham at 830-798-3654 if you are interested in seeing it in person. ALL proceeds will directly benefit the students in the MFISD construction trades program.

Upon sale, the buyer is solely responsible for removal and transportation of home. Home must be moved within 30 days of purchase. Buyer must secure a valid insurance policy within 72 hours of purchase. Buyer should be aware of any zoning or deed restrictions that may prohibit placement of the home on their property. Buyer is responsible for any and all associated permits, fees, and utility connections onsite. Home sold as is, where is.

post_text:
We have been getting some questions about the reduced Marble Falls ISD tax rate and “frozen” property taxes for those over the age of sixty-five. To be clear, although “re-freezing” may be an option for some, in most cases the increase in overall property values over the past several years would make it less expensive to pay taxes at your current “frozen” amount.
Be sure to check with the Burnet County Appraisal District to determine which would best benefit you before making any changes.
Please share this information as appropriate.

post_text:
In April we convened a Facilities Planning Committee made up of Marble Falls community members, business leaders, Marble Falls ISD staff and parents to evaluate and prioritize the current and future needs of the district. The committee evaluated different options to address those needs and presented a recommendation to the Board on July 16, 2018 as to how to proceed with a long-range plan and the need for a bond election.

With that in mind, we would like your opinion concerning our facility needs. We’ve partnered with an independent polling firm to help us gauge what you think about the district and options being considered. Please take a few minutes to complete this brief, but very important survey. (The survey is completely anonymous.)

Your opinion matters!

Please complete the survey found at the link below no later than July 31st. Surveys submitted after that date cannot be included in the findings.

https://www.research.net/r/MarbleFalls2018c
